      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> Need to wait for retest to pass before I can edit the commit message.\n> If you provide the CoverityID: I can edit the commit message without losing the reviews.  That said, pushing a new patch witg *only* a new commit message and/or trivial rebase will not lose the reviews either, if the patch needs to be retested.\n\nSorry. I missed your comment. All comments does not show up in my email (although I have tuned the setting for it, I used to get it earlier). And once it gets the required review, it loses focus. :-(. I know this is done now, I thought I let you know. The 'C' in CID is short for 'Coverity' in CoverityID the numerical ID remains the same. Just wanted to save space.",
